               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-226-person2109">
                  CHARLOTTE 
                  BARFORD
               <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2109" type="surname" value="BARFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2109" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2109" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in <placeName id="t18200412-226-crimeloc1304">Gloucester-buildings, Whitecross-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-226-crimeloc1304" type="placeName" value="Gloucester-buildings, Whitecross-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200412-226-crimeloc1304" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-226-off1302 t18200412-226-crimeloc1304"></join>. I lost the shirt out of the yard on the 7th of March - it is a court-yard, and has no thoroughfare; I saw the prisoner in the yard, but never saw him before. I saw him break the line, take the shirt, and run away with it. I opened the door, ran after him, and saw him going into a coffee-shop with it under his arm. I got an officer, and found the shirt on the floor of the coffee-shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-226-person2110">
                  GEORGE 
                  MOORE
               <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2110" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2110" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2110" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pipemaker. I was in Chequer-alley, by the coffee-shop, and saw the prisoner run into it with something under his jacket. Mrs. Barford overtook him going into the coffee-shop, and charged him with stealing the shirt.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-226-person2111">
                  JAMES 
                  HADLEY
               <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2111" type="surname" value="HADLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2111" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200412-226-person2111" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was desired by Mrs. Barford to apprehend the prisoner - there were about twelve others in the room. When I went in I told all the persons to stand up, and she pointed out the prisoner as the lad. I found the shirt just under him, it was wet.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The woman and the constable came in, and pointed me out as the person without a hat; there were several others in the same room without hats.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200412-226-verdict1305" type="verdictDescription">
